Here,1.... we connect to aws account through aws cli 
-- - need to install aws cli commands 1 sudo apt update
----2. sudo apt install curl unzip
-----3.curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
-----4.unzip awscliv2.zip
-----5.sudo ./aws/install && aws --version
-----6. aws configure
you connect to aws account 
then now create ec2 instance and s3 bucket or any thing based on required
For EC2 Instance - aws ec2 run-instances --image-id ami-xxxxxxxxxx --count 1 --instance-type t2.micro --key-name xxxxxx --security-group-ids sg-xxxxxxxxx --subnet-id subnet-xxxxxxx 
   for tags -- aws ec2 create-tags --resources i-xxxxxx --tags Key=Name,Value=MyInstance
For s3 bucket - aws s3api create-bucket --bucket your-bucket-name --region your-region --create-bucket-configuration LocationConstraint=your-region
###* For refrence kindly check the aws cli documention *###33
